@@TJvFatalAppExit
<GROUP TJvFatalAppExit>
Summary
  TJvFatalAppExit is a wrapper for the Windows 'program error' dialog.
Description
  TJvFatalAppExit is a wrapper for the Windows 'program error' dialog.  It
  enables the developer to display a customised program error message within
  a modal dialog.

  The developer needs to set the value of the string which will be contained
  within the program error dialog prior to displaying the dialog.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFatalAppExit.Execute
Summary
  Use this method to display a modal program error dialog with customised text.
Description
  Use this method is display a modal program error dialog with customised text.

  The dialog can be displayed only at run time. Attempts to display the dialog at
  design time will elicit the error message "Unable to call Execute at
  design-time!"
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFatalAppExit.Text
Summary
  Contains the text to be displayed in the program error dialog.
Description
  Contains the text to be displayed in the program error dialog. No limit is
  placed on the length of the text to be displayed. The elicited program error
  dialog will be sized around the text.  This means that if the
  text the developer has selected is too long to be displayed on the user's
  screen the left and right hand sided of the dialog will not be visible.
Parameters
  Text - The message which the program error dialog is to display.
